HEADWORD: Endogeny
<hw>En*dog"e*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Endogenesis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Growth from within;
multiplication of cells by endogenous division, as in the development of
one or more cells in the interior of a parent cell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

